#+COMMENT:                                                            -*- org -*-
#+TITLE: Hacking Dezyne command line tools

* Regression test

    make check

Run an individual test

   ./pre-inst-env run test/all/hello

Re-run all failures (e.g., after making fixes)

    make recheck

Run all parser tests

    make check FULL_TESTS="$(cd test/parser; ls -1)"

Run all verification failure tests

    make check FULL_TESTS="$(cd test/error; ls -1)"

* Binary releases
Moved to pack.git
* Documentation

** For the Dezyne manual, do something like:

#+BEGIN_SRC bash
$(grep -o 'guix time.*' *.scm) --ad-hoc texlive-bin texlive-base texlive-tex-plain texlive-tex-texinfo texlive-epsf rsync
./autogen.sh
./configure
git clean -fdx -- doc
make info html pdf
make publish SITE=kluit.dezyne.org:/srv/dezyne.org/site/dezyne
#+END_SRC

** For the dezyne.org website

#+BEGIN_SRC bash
git clone kluit.dezyne.org:~janneke/src/web/dezyne.org.git
cd dezyne.org
guix environment -m guix.scm
make
make serve # => check localhost:8888
make publish
#+END_SRC

** Importing texinfo, e.g. from DOCX

To try automatic conversion using pandoc, e.g., do something like
#+BEGIN_SRC bash
guix environment --ad-hoc ghc-pandoc -- pandoc ~/src/verum/DezyneTutorial/Code_Integration_Complete.docx -o doc/dezyne-tutorial-code-integration.texi
<add boilerplates, remove manually created TOC, remove silly anchors, stuff>
<lotsa manual editing; steal from doc/dezyne.texi>
<add license, etc.>
Use: M-x texinfo-all-menus-update RET

Look at
  * https://git.savannah.gnu.org/cgit/guix.git/tree/doc/guix.texi
  * https://guix.gnu.org/manual/en/html_node/

and steal ideas for index, programmers index, syntax/keyword highligting in html, etc.

#+END_SRC

